# ── Dorc .gitignore ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Initial safety-snapshot excludes reproducible / locked / large artifacts.
# The measurement corpus itself is NEVER committed: it lives out-of-tree (an
# XDG cache), pinned only by an in-tree manifest. See the spike charter.

# Vendored upstream tools. Reproducible via Research/clone-vendor.sh; each subdir
# is its own upstream git repo (would otherwise become a stray gitlink); and these
# two trees are the known Syncthing lock/churn source the charter warns about.
/Vendor/
/Research/Vendor/

# Python virtualenv for the PDF-extraction helpers. The .pdf-extract/*.py scripts
# are kept; the venv is reproducible and ~74M.
/.pdf-extract/venv/

# Machine-local Claude Code settings (a shared .claude/settings.json, if added, is kept).
/.claude/settings.local.json

# Guard against accidentally committing an in-tree corpus cache.
/.cache/
